# M015 Failure Ledger
## Verification snapshot
| Command | Exit | Result | What it showed |
|---|---:|---|---|
| `cargo test --test patamon_blueprint_seam --test holy_support_resolution --test holy_support_roster_contract --test holy_support_affordance --test event_stream --test twin_core_mechanics --test twin_core_integration --test validation_snapshot --test battery_loop_kernel --test predator_loop_kernel && python3 scripts/verify_combat_authority_audit.py` | 0 | ✅ pass | The targeted S03 authority suite is green: custom signals parse, Patamon blueprint dispatch reaches Holy Support state/snapshots, lifecycle beats and kernel transitions are live, Twin Core current fields are asserted, runtime registration populates kernel resources, and the strengthened authority verifier passes. |
| `python3 scripts/verify_combat_authority_audit.py` | 0 | ✅ pass | The tracked verifier confirms requirement coverage, drift rows D1-D11, tracked evidence paths, placeholder absence, and claim-scoped S03 markers for seeded Patamon blueprint dispatch, live beat/kernel events, Holy Support snapshots, and downstream boundaries. |
| `cargo test --test combat_cli_shared_surface --test presentation_metadata_boundary --test event_stream --test patamon_blueprint_seam && python3 scripts/verify_combat_authority_audit.py && python3 scripts/verify_m015_failure_ledger.py` | 0 | ✅ pass | The targeted S05 proof bundle is green: the real `combat_cli` binary emits shared action affordance, action/damage/cast event, `OnCombatBeat`, `OnKernelTransition`, and `[CLI_PROOF] validation_snapshot:` markers from a non-root cwd; the docs/verifiers preserve the S06 full-suite boundary. |
| `BEVYROGUE_JSONL=1 BEVYROGUE_CLI_PROOF=1 cargo run --bin combat_cli` | 0 | ✅ pass | The direct proof command exercises the real CLI proof mode and emits stable shared-surface markers including `Action affordances`, `OnActionResolved`, `OnDamageDealt`, `OnSkillCast`, `[CLI_PROOF] validation_snapshot:`, and `holy_support=grace=` without SkillBook fallback or readiness failure text. |
| `cargo test --no-run` | 101 | ❌ fail | The whole suite still stops on pre-existing broad-suite blockers. Across T05 no-run probes, Cargo reported missing docs include `docs/combat_ui_readiness_gap_matrix.md`, broad `SkillDef` constructors missing `custom_signals`, `animation_sequence`, and/or `qte`, broad `UnitDef` constructors missing `holy_support` and `twin_core`, and duplicate `UnitDef` fields in `tests/follow_up_chains.rs`. These are outside the now-green targeted S03/S05 authority contracts and remain assigned to S06. |
