# Presentation metadata boundary
## Cold invariant
## What RON may declare
| RON surface | Category | Allowed consumers | Boundary |
|---|---|---|---|
| Effects, targeting, costs, damage tags | Declarative gameplay content | Action query, resolution, state appliers | May affect legality and outcomes through typed Rust code. |
| `custom_signals` | Typed gameplay intent | Per-Digimon blueprint Rust modules, then kernel transitions | May affect outcomes only after a typed blueprint maps the signal to canonical transitions. |
| `animation_sequence` | Presentation metadata | UI, CLI, animation, log narration, accessibility-friendly presentation layers | Must not affect legality, damage, status, resources, kernel state, or snapshots. |
| `qte` | Presentation metadata | UI/CLI prompts and input affordance descriptions | Must not grant success, resources, damage, status, or transitions by itself. |
| Presentation trigger wording | Presentation metadata | Display timing, copy, tutorials, narration | Must not become a parser for gameplay commands. |
## Beats are canonical lifecycle output, not presentation ownership
## Typed custom signals are the extension seam
## Executable proof
## Reader check

